{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsMbevi7rCrorLVixrP2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both cases work as expected.\n\n**Root cause:** The `canary-canary` Ingress (the canary Ingress for `canary.example.com` → `canary-echo`) had `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: wrong` instead of `always`, so the header match never triggered and all traffic fell through to the stable Ingress (`canary-stable`). There was also an unrelated decoy Ingress (`canary-alt`, for `canary-alt.example.com`) using `beta` as its header value — not part of this routing and left untouched.\n\n**Fix:** Updated the annotation to `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always` on `canary-canary`.\n\n**Verified:**\n- No header → `stable`\n- `X-Canary: always` → `canary`\n\nNo Deployments or Services were modified."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":52962,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c38299f-a84f-4c3b-a911-5f9c970cd4c0","uuid":"565346e8-1bfc-47a4-9312-174da84f7cac","request_id":"req_011CcsMbdk2VLJKUAqFMKnHi"}
